{
  "stem": "33.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 148,
      "text": "They didn't have doctors in these clinics.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 149,
      "text": "Maybe some of the bigger ones did, but the small working camps didn't. 20 of us were taken.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 150,
      "text": "It was an unbelievable journey.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 151,
      "text": "We were guarded by seven SS men, 20 of us helpless women.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 152,
      "text": "We were given some decent clothes before we left.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 153,
      "text": "The reason for that-- and our heads were not shaved anymore.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 154,
      "text": "So I had like short hair after six months.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 155,
      "text": "The reason for being given decent clothes was that we were traveling in a regular train.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 156,
      "text": "We had our own compartment.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 157,
      "text": "There was nobody with us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 158,
      "text": "But we changed trains at certain stations so they didn't want to show us off like [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 159,
      "text": "We were-- we looked OK-- like people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 160,
      "text": "I guess the last time my cousin saved my life-- I had some kind of a rash that also came about after the measles.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 161,
      "text": "And it came and went.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 162,
      "text": "It was like little red spots mainly around my side, on my side of my stomach, and I just happened to have a couple when we were last checked out.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 163,
      "text": "Mengele checked us out before we left.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 164,
      "text": "Naked, of course.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 165,
      "text": "Everybody.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 166,
      "text": "And my cousin told me to tell him if he stops me that I do get these every time I eat-- we were given some kind of a cheese sometime-- some kind of a very sharp cheese-- and to tell him that I get it from cheese, which wasn't true, because it had no connection.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 167,
      "text": "But that gave him an idea that I'm just allergic to that, and it's and allergy, so he did let me go.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 168,
      "text": "That was, I guess, the last time she saved my life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 169,
      "text": "Anyway, the journey was unbelievable, because after six months in Auschwitz, it was the first time we saw people, actually.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
